# AutoBug AI Architectural Overhaul Plan (Phases 1–10)

This plan defines a complete redesign of the AutoBug AI pipeline to resolve report inconsistency, speculative claims, false approvals, and arbitrary confidence scores by establishing a **Single Source of Truth** state.

---

## Shared Architecture Vision

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Issue & Repo Inputs] --> B[Environment & Build Check]
    B --> C[Reproduction Agent & Logs]
    C --> D[Evidence Collector]
    D --> E[Root Cause & Localization]
    E --> F[Patch Generator]
    F --> G[Validation Engine]
    G --> H[Strict Reviewer Agent]
    H --> I[Risk Analysis Agent]
    I --> J[Confidence Engine]
    J --> K[Consistency Checker]
    K --> L[Jinja Report Generator]
    L --> M[Git & PR Branching]
```

---

## Proposed Changes & Phases

### Phase 1 — Shared Pydantic Model State (Single Source of Truth)
Establish a structured schema for the entire pipeline state to ensure agents write to predefined JSON structures instead of free-text Markdown.

#### [NEW] [schemas.py](file:///c:/Users/ankit/Desktop/AutoBug/backend/app/agents/schemas.py)
* Define Pydantic models for validation state, reproduction logs, review feedback, execution metrics, and risk analysis parameters:
```python
class ValidationState(BaseModel):
    tests_executed: bool = False
    tests_passed: bool = False
    failed_reason: str | None = None
    coverage: float | None = None

class ReproductionEvidence(BaseModel):
    command: str
    reproduced: bool
    observed_output: str
    expected_output: str
    request_details: str | None = None
```

#### [MODIFY] [state.py](file:///c:/Users/ankit/Desktop/AutoBug/backend/app/agents/state.py)
* Refactor `AutoBugState` to hold these typed schema objects, converting the pipeline into a strictly typed LangGraph state machine.

