### Phase 3 — Rule-Based Confidence Engine
Replace arbitrary LLM-generated confidence scores with an objective programmatic scoring matrix.

#### [NEW] [confidence.py](file:///c:/Users/ankit/Desktop/AutoBug/backend/app/core/confidence.py)
* Implement a programmatic confidence score calculator:
  - Bug Reproduced in Sandbox: `+20%`
  - Stacktrace Captured: `+10%`
  - Root cause file/line localized: `+20%`
  - Static Analysis Passed: `+15%`
  - Validation Tests Passed: `+25%`
  - Reviewer Approved: `+10%`
  - **Penalty:** Cap at `65%` if tests failed to execute or failed to pass.

---

### Phase 4 — Improved Reviewer Agent
Ensure the Reviewer Agent relies strictly on source diffs and test results without speculative reasoning.

#### [MODIFY] [reviewer_agent.py](file:///c:/Users/ankit/Desktop/AutoBug/backend/app/agents/reviewer_agent.py)
* Rewrite the Reviewer system prompt to only evaluate the AST differences and validation command logs.
* Require the Reviewer to output a strictly structured evaluation schema: approved status, correctness, security, maintainability, performance, evidence, and suggestions.
* Align scores (e.g. 7-8/10 for minor feedback, <5/10 only for compile errors/syntax bugs).

